			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Howdy all, just a quick question regarding the pet hold command.
<br />

<br />
I have access to a friend's account who retired not too long ago, and he has a level 63 necro with a considerable amount of AA's.  Recently, I've been logging onto his account to test out his various AA's to see which ones I might like to get.  However, I have yet to figure out what I'm doing wrong with the pet hold command.  
<br />

<br />
It seems to work, at best, sporadically.  Sometimes the pet seems to decide to defend me despite my commands, and occasionally it will hold for a few moments, only to join in later in the battle for no apparant reason.  Is there a trick to this that I am just not getting?
<br />

<br />
Note that none of the mobs I'm fighting have any kind of AoE.  Also, this has only really happened to me in Rujarkian adventures, but I haven't really tested it elsewhere.<br />_________________<br />Murder is like any odd looking food -- you don't know you have a taste for it until you've tried it.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
