			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sorry guys, but I have to correct you on this one.
<br />

<br />
Best way to make hot buttons is 2, namely:
<br />

<br />
/Pet hold
<br />

<br />
and:
<br />

<br />
/Pet backoff
<br />
/Pet attack
<br />

<br />

<br />
Let me explain:
<br />

<br />
If you have a hot button with /pet hold or /pet back off &amp; /pet hold, than you might still get your pet attacking the wrong mob, specially when lots of adds are inc and you have to assist the MT.
<br />

<br />
Lets take VT for example. 
<br />

<br />
5 mobs inc, 1 for the MT, 3 for offtankers and 1 can be mezzed. Those 3 off-tank mobs all do AE casting. Now it can go wrong in many ways, but lets just say it goes wrong immediatly. You hit your /pet back off &amp; /pet hold (or vice versa) hotbutton before the pull off-course!
<br />

<br />
Now the mobs coming in and your pet gets hit by an AE spell from one of the off tanking mobs where you dont want your pet on, you want to assist the MT. The MT calls: All assist me on &lt;MOB X&gt;. You hit your assist button and get the MT's target. You hit /pet attack....... WTF your pet is going to the mob who just before hit him with an AE spell. Its an offtank mob, and even worse, that offtank mob will gate on low HP bringing lots of friends to your raidforce.
<br />

<br />
So to be 99,99% sure that your mob is attacking the MT's target make these 2 hot buttons:
<br />

<br />
/pet hold
<br />
&amp;
<br />
/pet backoff
<br />
/pet attack
<br />

<br />
You set the pets aggro on zero just before giving the attack call on a target, thats almost 100% save.
<br />

<br />
I know this goes for specially on adds/offtanking/AE mobs, but I think they are not only in VT. Think about it, I am using these 2 hot buttons and I never have problems getting my pet on the MT's target.
<br />

<br />
P.S. It would be nice though to adjust the /pet commands in the pet window, since you can give them while casting. I would love to get a 
<br />

<br />
/pet hold-
<br />
&amp;
<br />
/pet back off
<br />
/pet attack-
<br />

<br />
button in the petwindow. Than I could control my pet while I am casting. Thats imo the only downside to my 2 hotbuttons, they are both not "hittable" when casting.<br />_________________<br />Its better to remain silent and be thought a fool, than to speak and remove all doubt (Lincoln)
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=192929" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nebukad Nezzer</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
