<br />
Wouldn't work too well for me, I use both a pet attack hotkey and I also type /pet attack.  When I want to sic my pet during casting, I type it out.  Useful for pulling, Black ceramic band till mob is close to camp, start casting snare, as mob is close to me (maybe about to hit me), I sic my pet.  Pet eats HT if there is one, snare lands, and mob starts chasing me again.
<br />

<br />
Some times my pet makes contact before the spell, some times not, but in any event, typing it out gives you control over when you send your pet even when you're casting.  You'd be surprised how fast you can type this when you use it all the time.
<br />

<br />
So for me it's 
<br />
/pet hold
<br />
/pet back off
<br />

<br />
and this works fine.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://lotgd.net" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.odgclients.com/xeric/portraits/Medallion-Animated.gif" border="0" />  Slay a dragon ... over lunch!</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
