<br />
In my experienc, that's the problem.  Until recently, EC LDoN Adventueres have been bugged for pets.  I've had my pet sudden;y run off and start attacking random mobs in these adventures.  For a while, I just stopped using a pet all together in EC.  Not to long ago, this has been fixed.
<br />

<br />
However, there is still something wrong with the mechanics of /pet hold.  If, for example, you're in Siren's Grotto, tell your pet to back off and hold on a Seahorse and get out of the water, your pet is still targetting the Seahorse.  So the next time you tell it to attack, it'll flip out and run the opposite direction towards that Seahorse.  I havn't figured out a way to make it go for the new trget, yet.  My pet always keps that first target.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=611349" target="_blank" class="postlink">Lich Carnox Sol'Reaver - Proud  Lizard Lich of Invictus Verite</a>
